ered by electrons of energies up to\nabout 10$^{14}$ eV by the inverse Compton (IC) process. The observed flux of\nthe TeV gamma rays, together with that of the non-thermal X-rays, gives firm\nconstraints on the acceleration process in the SNR shell; a magnetic field of\n$6.5\\pm2$ $\\mu$G is inferred from both the synchrotron X-rays and inverse\nCompton TeV gamma-rays, which gives entirely consistent mechanisms that\nelectrons of energies up to 10$^{14}$ eV are produced via the shock\nacceleration in SN1006.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Jan 1998 11:43:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-04-04"}
